result.execSummary:
The defendant David J. Gonzales was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

10:01 AM DA Kelz calls cases 16CF83, 16CM104 and states appearances. Defendant David J. Gonzales appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states these matters are set for a return on warrant/ initial appearance. Court questions defendant on non-appearance. Defendant gives responses. DA Kelz motions to quash the warrant. So Ordered. court states charges and maximum penalties. Defendant states he has not received complaints in either complaint. DA Kelz states he was personally served the complaints back in 2016. Complaints acknowledged, reading waived. DA Kelz requests these cases track together. So ordered. DA Kelz requests a $600 cash bond be set for both cases together. So ordered. Defendant objects to the statements made by the State and the monetary amount requested. Court questions defendant on ties to the County. Defendant gives responses. Court orders cash bond in the amount of $400. In case 16CF83 Preliminary hearing requested, time limits NOT waived. Notice of right to attorney given to DE.
